  "text": "One who cuts his nails, his hair, his mustache or his beard is surely [doing] a subcategory of shearing, so he is liable. And that is when he cuts with a tool. But if he cuts with his hand – whether himself or someone else – he is exempt. Likewise one who cuts off a growth from his body is exempt – whether by hand or with a tool, whether from himself or from someone else. And it is permissible to cut off a growth in the Temple by hand, but not with a tool. However if it was dry, he may even cut it off with a tool and [then] perform the [Temple] service.",
